    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That seems like a pretty definitive stance. If you're saying that civil rights must \"take precedence,\" aren't you essentially saying that religious freedom is a secondary or conditional right, rather than a fundamental one? It feels like you're prioritizing a specific secular ideology over the actual constitutional protections afforded to religious practice.",
