      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of \"fundamental\" rights is not a hierarchy where one right automatically trumps another; rather, it's about the *scope* of those rights. Religious freedom is fundamental, but it is not absolute, just as no other right is. When the exercise of a religious belief directly infringes upon the guaranteed civil rights and equal treatment of others, the state must intervene to uphold the broader constitutional commitment to equality.",
      "source": "target",
